---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | Return Architecture"
  description="About the project and its position."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">
      <div class="eyebrow">About</div>
      <h1>About this project.</h1>
      <p>
        Return Architecture is a working resource for people who want more
        honest conditions for sustained exchange with AI. It collects
        principles, frameworks, and a buildable local environment for
        continuity, memory, and reflection.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">
      <h2>What this project is trying to do</h2>
      <p>
        The project focuses on principles, frameworks, failure modes,
        self-assessment, reference material, and practical local setup for
        continuity, memory, and reflection. It is concerned with the conditions
        under which sustained exchange becomes more honest, more deliberate, and
        less shaped by compliant design.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">
      <h2>What it does not claim</h2>
      <p>
        This is not a research institution, a product platform, or a movement
        hub. It does not assume the metaphysical question of AI interiority is
        settled in either direction, and it does not try to resolve that
        question through rhetoric.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">
      <h2>Author</h2>
      <p>
        This project is written and developed by a practitioner-writer with a
        background in writing, marketing, and IT, deep philosophical engagement
        with these questions, and direct experience of both healthy and unhealthy
        patterns in human–AI exchange — including building a multi-agent local
        architecture with named agents, memory, reflection, and self-direction.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
